@page "/privacy"

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy</PageTitle>

<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

<p>
    This project is primarily educational. The deployed demonstration should not be used to process
    sensitive personal data unless you adapt hosting, retention, and legal controls for your context.
</p>

<h2>Data processed</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Authentication data (email, hashed password, token metadata).</li>
    <li>Application usage and audit data (security and operational traces).</li>
    <li>Error monitoring events when Sentry is configured.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Purpose</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Authenticate users and enforce authorization rules.</li>
    <li>Operate and secure the service.</li>
    <li>Diagnose incidents and improve reliability.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Retention and deletion</h2>
<p>
    Data retention depends on your deployment configuration. If you run this project, define and
    document your retention policy and deletion workflow before production use.
</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>
    For privacy questions, use the project contact channels listed on the
    <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>.
</p>
